main event: An unidentified aerial phenomenon was observed in Gurnee, Illinois on August 11, 1955.
interesting points: The object was described as having both linear and elliptical shapes., The object appeared to be traveling at varying speeds and courses across the sky., Witness saw the object for approximately 2-3 minutes., The object emitted lights, although no positive identification could be made., The witness described the object as possibly being an unconventional type of aircraft.
